+Head('Tonic')

body#tonic
  +Header('Tonic')
  
  main
    .flex
      section.intro.flex-50.left
      section.intro.flex-50.right
        h1 Tonic
        .caption 
          | &mdash; UX/UI Design, Branding
          br
          | &mdash; Web Design and Development
    
    section.copy
      blockquote Tonic is a minimalist, stable component framework. It is about
        |  250 lines of code in total, and favours React-like component composition. 
      hr
      p Using my previous experience in designing application interfaces, my role
        |  in this project was designing and building out the default UI components
        |  and themes in the Tonic framework for use in future projects.
      
    section.copy
      h1 Visual Interface Design
      h2 Logo
      p tbd
      h2 Typography
      p tbd
      h2 Colour
      p tbd
      h2 Elements
      p The default form elements for Tonic components. Each element can be 
        |  customized (fonts, colours, etc) and I wanted to create a solid
        |  base that is well-designed and commincative but also a good canvas
        |  for user customization.
      p All components were also designed and developed to include keyboard support.
  
